" Further settings are based upon this guide:
" https://towardsdatascience.com/the-essential-ideavim-remaps-291d4cd3971b

"" Common settings -------------------------
set clipboard+=unnamed
set clipboard+=ideaput
set scrolloff=5
set incsearch " highlight the search string while typing
set number relativenumber

" Editing and Reloading the Config ===================================
" Author of this ideavim guide uses prefix \ for commands he doesn't use while coding
nnoremap \e :e ~/.ideavimrc<CR> " open .ideavimrc
nnoremap \r :action IdeaVim.ReloadVimRc.reload<CR> " reload ideavimrc
" ====================================================================

" The Leader Key =====================================================
let mapleader=" "
" ====================================================================

" The Distraction Free / Zen mode ===================================
" Author and me like Vim's clean interface, and widgets of IDE may distract you. Plus, having visible widgets can
" ‘trick’ you to use the mouse instead of using a shortcut. Always remember: You can't click on what you can't see.
" nnoremap <c-z> :action ToggleDistractionFreeMode<CR> " Distraction free mode
nnoremap <c-z> :action ToggleZenMode<CR> " Zen mode
" ====================================================================

" Terminal ===========================================================
" Opening terminal
nnoremap <c-t> :action ActivateTerminalToolWindow<CR>
" Action Terminal.OpenInTerminal open a new terminal directly in the parent folder of the current file in the editor.
" This is very useful with deeply nested folder structures, since it avoids having to cd to the right folder.
nnoremap <leader>t :action Terminal.OpenInTerminal<CR>
" ====================================================================

" Window Navigation ==================================================
" Splitting windows
nnoremap <c-\> :action SplitVertically<CR>
nnoremap <c--> :action SplitHorizontally<CR>
nnoremap <c-=> :action Unsplit<CR>

" The sethandler command sets IdeaVim as the handler of the specified shortcut. This can be done via the settings UI.
" However, Author and I like to keep everything in one place as much as possible.
nnoremap <c-m> :action MoveEditorToOppositeTabGroup<CR>
" Navigating between splitted windows via ctrl-h/j/k/l
sethandler <c-j> a:vim
sethandler <c-k> a:vim
nnoremap <c-h> <c-w>h
nnoremap <c-l> <c-w>l
nnoremap <c-j> <c-w>j
nnoremap <c-k> <c-w>k

" Next and previous tab
nnoremap <TAB> :action NextTab<CR>
nnoremap <s-TAB> :action PreviousTab<CR>

nnoremap<Leader>en :action EditSourceInNewWindow<CR> " Open current file in new window
nnoremap <Leader>n :action NextWindow<CR> " Go to next opened window

nnoremap <Leader>q :action CloseContent<CR> " Не уверен, что делает этот shortcut
nnoremap <Leader>qa :action CloseAllEditors<CR>
" ====================================================================

" Editing Source Code ================================================
" ideajoin` Boolean (default false). If true, join command will be performed via IDE.
" Action is called by default as ctrl + shift + J.  This is smart-feature, behaves differently under different
" circumstances. You can see examples here - https://github.com/JetBrains/ideavim/wiki/%22ideajoin%22-examples
set ideajoin
" Define the mode that would be enabled during the refactoring (renaming, live template, introduce variable, etc).
" - keep  - keep the mode that was enabled before starting a refactoring.
set idearefactormode=keep

" Press < and > in Visual mode to move selected text Tab left and right
vnoremap < <gv
vnoremap > >gv

nnoremap [[ :action MethodUp<CR>
nnoremap ]] :action MethodDown<CR>

nnoremap zc :action CollapseRegion<CR>
nnoremap zo :action ExpandRegion<CR>
nnoremap <leader>zc :action CollapseAllRegions<CR>
nnoremap <leader>zo :action ExpandAllRegions<CR>

nnoremap <leader>c :action CommentByLineComment<CR>

" Popub refactor optons
nnoremap <leader>r :action Refactorings.QuickListPopupAction<CR>

nnoremap <Leader>=  :action ReformatCode<CR>
nnoremap <leader>o :action OptimizeImports<CR>

" nnoremap <c-r> :action RecentFiles<CR>
nnoremap <c-e> :action RecentFiles<CR> " Remapped RecentFiles to c-e because c-r is for undoing undo (undo = u)
nnoremap <leader>l :action RecentLocations<CR>
nnoremap <leader>h  :action LocalHistory.ShowHistory<CR>

nnoremap ge :action GotoNextError<CR>
nnoremap gE :action GotoPreviousError<CR>
" ===================================================================e

" Searching and Source Code Navigation ===============================
nnoremap <c-/> :action FindInPath<CR>
nnoremap <c-a> :action GotoAction<CR>
nnoremap <c-f> :action GotoFile<CR>
nnoremap <leader>u :action FindUsages<CR>

nnoremap <leader>s :action GotoRelated<CR>
nnoremap <leader>h :action CallHierarchy<CR>
nnoremap <leader>b :action ShowNavBar<CR>
nnoremap <c-s> :action FileStructurePopup<CR>
nnoremap <c-o> :action GotoSymbol<CR>
nnoremap gc :action GotoClass<CR>
nnoremap gi :action GotoImplementation<CR>
nnoremap gd :action GotToDeclaration<CR>
nnoremap gp :action GotToSuperMethod<CR>
nnoremap gt :action GotoTest<CR>
nnoremap gb :action Back<CR>
nnoremap gf :action Forward<CR>
" ====================================================================

" Tool Windows =======================================================
nnoremap <c-p> :action JumpToLastWindow<CR>
nnoremap <c-x> :action HideAllWindows<CR>

" Other very important mappings for managing tool windows, that were configured in two ways:
" 1. Settings > Keymap > Other > Tool Windows View Mode:
"   Dock pinned = alt-d
"   Dock float = alt-f
"   Dock window = alt-w
" 2. Settings > Keymap > Main Window > Hide Active Tool Window:
"   Hide Active Tool Window = alt-h
" ====================================================================

" Running And Debugging ==============================================
nnoremap ,r :action ContextRun<CR> " Runs code under cursor
" Author uses ContextRun instead of Run, because the latter runs the previously selected configuration instead of
" running the code at the cursor
nnoremap ,c :action RunClass<CR> " It is NOT running class, it is for running CURRENT FILE
nnoremap ,f :action ChooseRunConfiguration<CR> " Chooses AND runs configuration
nnoremap ,t :action ActivateRunToolWindow<CR> " Show run configuration results window
nnoremap ,u :action Rerun<CR>
" All above commands apply to running tests
" ====================================================================
